cs.AR, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.SY

This paper proposes a reinforcement learning-based approach for warp scheduling in GPUs. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following sub-categories:

- cs.AR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): This sub-category includes papers on machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are relevant to the proposed approach.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category includes papers on reinforcement learning, which is the main technique used in the proposed approach.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): This sub-category includes papers on parallel computing, which is the context of the proposed approach.
- cs.PF (Performance): This sub-category includes papers on performance optimization, which is the goal of the proposed approach.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): This sub-category includes papers on control systems, which is relevant to the scheduling problem addressed in the proposed approach.
